THIRD-PARTY COMPONENTS
────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

modelchain has ZERO required runtime dependencies. The provider adapters and
the Vercel AI SDK adapter use OPTIONAL peer dependencies, resolved only when
the matching entry point is imported by the consumer. Each is distributed
under its own license:

  - openai (OpenAI)               — Apache-2.0
  - @anthropic-ai/sdk (Anthropic) — MIT
  - @google/genai (Google)        — Apache-2.0
  - ai (Vercel AI SDK)            — Apache-2.0
  - @ai-sdk/provider (Vercel)     — Apache-2.0

The core package, the streaming layer, the tool calling layer, and the generic
HTTP adapter use only the runtime's built-in fetch and Web Streams APIs; they
pull in none of the above.

